## Factionless roster: original creature lines (not from the source doc),
## 8 per category × 6 categories = 48 — parity with each of the other
## three factions' 48. Every line is anchored to a genuine public-domain
## mythological figure (centuries-to-millennia-old folklore, no modern
## copyrighted characterization), spanning Norse, Greek, Egyptian,
## Mesopotamian, Canaanite, Hindu, Aztec/Mesoamerican, Japanese, Yoruba/
## West African, Celtic, Slavic, Polynesian, and Maori traditions —
## deliberately avoiding Yahweh and any pop-culture-loaded reinterpretation
## (e.g. no "Morpheus," no franchise-flavored tricksters). The creature
## designs and all prose are original.
const FACTIONLESS_LINES: Array[Dictionary] = [
	{id="FL-EN1", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Thorling", desc="A stout, broad-shouldered figure crackling with restrained static, knuckles wrapped in strips of storm-scarred leather. Distant thunder answers every footstep, though the sky above stays clear."}, {name="Thorhammar", desc="Lightning now arcs constantly between its clenched fists, and each step leaves a scorched footprint of fulgurite glass. Storm clouds gather directly overhead wherever it stands."}, {name="Thoraskr", desc="A titan wreathed in a permanent thunderhead, its heartbeat audible as rolling thunder for miles. Where it strikes the ground, lightning forks in the shape of a hammer and the air itself rings like struck bronze."}]},
	{id="FL-EN2", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Raling", desc="A slim, falcon-eyed figure whose skin holds the dull warmth of embers banked overnight — never quite going out. A faint solar disc rides just above its brow, more suggestion than object."}, {name="Rabarque", desc="The disc has lifted free and now orbits its head slowly, throwing a thin corona that lengthens every shadow it crosses into the shape of a noon sundial, regardless of the actual hour."}, {name="Raatum", desc="A towering solar herald whose disc has become a second sun low on the horizon, casting two shadows from everything nearby — one true, one running fast-forward through the day that hasn't happened yet."}]},
	{id="FL-EN3", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Amaling", desc="A softly luminous figure wrapped in layered silk-like light, retreating half a step whenever looked at directly, as if shy of being seen fully."}, {name="Amakagu", desc="The light has taken on a woven, mirror-bright quality, throwing back fractured reflections of whoever stands nearest — never quite their true expression."}, {name="Amaomikami", desc="A sunrise given a walking shape, so bright that looking at it directly leaves afterimages that linger for days, each afterimage whispering encouragement in a voice the observer almost recognizes as their own, kinder."}]},
	{id="FL-EN4", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Xiuhling", desc="A squat, sturdy figure wreathed in a low blue flame that never spreads to whatever it stands on, turquoise scales flickering across its forearms like dying coals."}, {name="Xiuhpilli", desc="The blue flame has climbed to a full mantle, and the turquoise scales have hardened into overlapping plates that chime like glass when it moves, a sound like a hearth about to become a wildfire."}, {name="Xiuhteotl", desc="An old-fire god scaled to a bonfire the height of a building, turquoise-plated and burning a blue so deep it reads as cold — anything it touches either catches instantly or frosts over, with no middle setting."}]},
	{id="FL-EN5", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Perling", desc="A broad-shouldered figure with an axe of grey stormcloud slung over one shoulder, hair that stands on end even in still air."}, {name="Perkuno", desc="Twin axes now, and small forks of lightning jump between its fingers when it clenches a fist, thunder arriving a half-second sooner than it should."}, {name="Perundubu", desc="An oak-rooted storm titan, its axes now full lightning bolts that never fully leave its hands, thunder arriving before the swing does — cause and effect have stopped agreeing on the order of things nearby."}]},
	{id="FL-EN6", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Sangoling", desc="A double-headed figure carrying a smoldering carved staff, each head watching a different direction at once."}, {name="Sangodara", desc="The staff now trails a ribbon of static-charged smoke, and each head speaks half a sentence the other completes, always about a storm arriving elsewhere."}, {name="Sangobalogun", desc="A twin-visaged storm-king whose staff has become a spinning column of ball lightning, both heads speaking in perfect unison now about storms that have already happened somewhere else and are still deciding to happen here."}]},
	{id="FL-EN7", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Belling", desc="A lean, sun-bright figure with a wheel-shaped halo that turns slowly whether or not there's any wind."}, {name="Belanu", desc="The wheel-halo has grown spokes of hard white light, and every few turns throws a spark that becomes, briefly, a second small sun hovering nearby before fading."}, {name="Belenios", desc="A midsummer titan crowned in a wheel of solid light the size of a chariot, throwing off sparks that become short-lived suns, each one aging a small patch of ground through an entire season before it gutters out."}]},
	{id="FL-EN8", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Huitzling", desc="A hummingbird-quick silhouette, iridescent feathers at the shoulders catching light that shouldn't be there in the shade."}, {name="Huitzilin", desc="The feathers have become a mantle of live embers shaped like wings, and its footsteps leave scorched hummingbird-prints that flare and vanish."}, {name="Huitzopochtli", desc="A war-sun titan robed in wings of solid flame, casting a light so directional that it creates a false noon in whichever direction it's decided the day should go."}]},
	{id="FL-ET1", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Motling", desc="A gaunt, ash-grey figure that moves like time-lapse decay — flowers wilt and paint peels in a slow ripple around its footsteps. Its eyes are twin hourglasses, sand perpetually falling."}, {name="Motharu", desc="The decay ripple has widened into a visible field; metal rusts and wood rots on contact within several paces. Its hourglass eyes have cracked, sand leaking as fine grey dust that never depletes."}, {name="Motabbir", desc="A colossal herald of ending, trailing a wake where entire seasons pass in seconds — crops ripen and rot, structures age to ruin. Its voice is the sound every clock makes in its final tick, heard simultaneously by everyone nearby."}]},
	{id="FL-ET2", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Ereshling", desc="A gaunt, veiled figure who leaves faint grey handprints on anything she brushes past — the exact texture things have after long neglect."}, {name="Ereshkatu", desc="The veil has become seven layered veils, each one shed only in a place utterly out of sight, and what's beneath is a little less finished each time."}, {name="Ereshkigla", desc="The Queen of a going-nowhere-fast, seven veils now permanently in motion around a form that gets vaguer the closer it's looked at, and every door it passes through remains permanently a little bit ajar, letting the cold out of somewhere else."}]},
	{id="FL-ET3", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Izaling", desc="A once-beautiful figure kept carefully in three-quarter profile, the unseen side clearly do not want to be looked at yet."}, {name="Izanagu", desc="Turning further reveals patches of quiet decay held together by will alone; she apologizes for it in a voice that is still, somehow, kind."}, {name="Izanamikoto", desc="She has stopped turning away. What was hidden is now simply what she is: a slow, dignified ruin that has made peace with rot, and offers the observer the same peace, whether or not they want it."}]},
	{id="FL-ET4", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Mictling", desc="A bone-thin figure in a paper collar, eye sockets a little too wide, always mid-smile."}, {name="Mictlanteo", desc="The bones have gone slightly translucent, faint marigold light behind the ribs, and the smile has widened past what a jaw should allow."}, {name="Mictlantecutli", desc="A skeletal lord of the deepest floor, wreathed in owl feathers and dim marigold light, whose smile has become the only expression left available to it — worn permanently over whatever it used to feel."}]},
	{id="FL-ET5", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Morrigling", desc="A crow-shouldered woman-shape at the edge of vision, always exactly three crows in the air nearby, never more, never fewer."}, {name="Morriwash", desc="The three crows have started landing in the exact spots someone is about to fall, an instant before they fall there."}, {name="Morriganu", desc="A battlefield made person, crow-cloaked and washing bloodied cloth in a stream that runs backward — whoever recognizes their own garment in her hands has already, in some sense, finished today."}]},
	{id="FL-ET6", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Chernoling", desc="A charcoal-dark shape that seems to absorb the light around lanterns rather than merely stand in shadow."}, {name="Chernobor", desc="The dark has thickened into a kind of smoke-armor, and small lights nearby gutter and require re-lighting twice as often as they should."}, {name="Chernobogu", desc="A black-god given full shape, wearing an armor of extinguished light — every flame within its reach burns a shade dimmer permanently after it passes, as if it kept a little of the light for itself."}]},
	{id="FL-ET7", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Oyaling", desc="A restless figure wrapped in nine skirts of wind-torn cloth, always slightly out of sync with the actual weather."}, {name="Oyabara", desc="The nine skirts have become a standing dust-devil that follows her exactly, tearing loose whatever wasn't already settled."}, {name="Oyansan", desc="A tempest-queen who arrives as her own weather front, nine winds at once, each one carrying off something different — memories, roof tiles, second chances — and depositing them somewhere she'll never say."}]},
	{id="FL-ET8", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Setling", desc="A rangy, sharp-snouted figure with reddish hide and an unplaceable, slightly wrong gait, like a familiar animal walking with borrowed legs."}, {name="Setekh", desc="The wrongness of the gait has spread to its whole silhouette, which now seems assembled from several different creatures that don't quite agree on scale."}, {name="Setutu", desc="A storm-red usurper-shape, composite and confident, whose every part is recognizable and whose whole is not — proof, it seems to argue by simply existing, that a good enough story doesn't need to make sense."}]},
	{id="FL-GR1", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Enkiling", desc="A slick, eel-smooth humanoid that never quite touches the ground, hovering in a shallow well of bent space that pools like water around its feet. Its voice carries a faint, layered echo, as if speaking from underwater."}, {name="Enkidapsu", desc="The gravity well beneath it has deepened into a visible depression that objects slowly slide toward. Its skin has taken on a deep-sea bioluminescence, patterns pulsing in rhythms too slow for human speech to match."}, {name="Enkiabzu", desc="A vast, tidal presence that bends the ground into a permanent basin, pulling loose objects and unbraced people toward its center in slow, inexorable orbits. It speaks in pressures felt in the chest rather than sound heard by the ear."}]},
	{id="FL-GR2", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Atling", desc="A stooped, immensely broad-shouldered figure perpetually bracing against a weight nobody else can see, knees never quite straightening."}, {name="Atlacos", desc="The unseen weight has started leaving actual impressions in solid stone beneath its feet, deep enough to hold rainwater."}, {name="Atlanteus", desc="A world-bearing titan frozen mid-effort, the ground around it permanently sloped inward as though everything nearby has already started, very slowly, to roll toward where it kneels."}]},
	{id="FL-GR3", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Taneling", desc="A slim, bark-skinned figure with roots instead of trailing hair, always standing at a slight, deliberate lean, as if propping something up."}, {name="Tanemahuta", desc="The lean has become permanent and structural — nearby trees list gently toward it, and the space around its shoulders reads subtly taller than everywhere else."}, {name="Tanewhakapiripiri", desc="A forest-father holding an invisible ceiling at arm's length, the space beneath him stretched a little higher than physics would otherwise allow — proof that the sky was, once, much closer, and someone had to move it."}]},
	{id="FL-GR4", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Tlalocling", desc="A round-eyed, fanged little figure that always stands in a personal patch of damp ground, however dry the surroundings."}, {name="Tlaloque", desc="The damp patch has become a standing puddle that mirrors clouds not actually in the sky, and small hailstones fall only within its reach."}, {name="Tlalocan", desc="A mountain-shaped rain-lord whose personal weather never leaves him, dragging a slow, localized deluge that pools uphill, against every rule water is supposed to follow."}]},
	{id="FL-GR5", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Gebling", desc="A reclining-postured figure who always seems slightly sunken into whatever surface he's on, as though standing were an ongoing negotiation."}, {name="Gebeb", desc="The sinking has become visible subsidence, soft depressions following him a few steps behind like slow footprints in solid rock."}, {name="Geburu", desc="An earth-father laid nearly flat by his own gravity, the ground for yards around him gently bowl-shaped, water and small objects alike drifting, unhurried, toward whichever way he's currently facing."}]},
	{id="FL-GR6", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Prithling", desc="A broad, patient figure who seems to be carrying an enormous, invisible flat weight balanced across both shoulders."}, {name="Prithumi", desc="The invisible weight now visibly bows the shoulders, and small stones nearby have begun to arrange themselves in the cardinal directions around her feet."}, {name="Prithvimata", desc="A world-mother bearing the whole flat weight of everywhere at once — a held breath given permanent shape, holding the horizon level purely through the effort of never once putting it down."}]},
	{id="FL-GR7", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Danuling", desc="A river-quiet figure whose footsteps sound like a distant waterfall no matter the terrain."}, {name="Danumor", desc="Small pools now form in her wake and drain toward her rather than downhill, and the waterfall-sound has grown loud enough to mask other noises nearby."}, {name="Danuannan", desc="A river-mother whose passage bends water itself against slope and sense, every stream nearby politely rerouting to pass beneath her feet, as though she were the actual lowest point in the world."}]},
	{id="FL-GR8", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Njording", desc="A weathered, sea-worn figure who leans into a wind that isn't blowing, boots always damp regardless of the ground."}, {name="Njorthar", desc="The lean has become a permanent list, like a ship keeling in harbor, and the damp has spread into a thin standing tide around each footprint."}, {name="Njordr", desc="A harbor-god keeled permanently to port, dragging a private tide that rises and falls to a moon only he can feel, pulling loose anything nearby that was never properly anchored down."}]},
	{id="FL-MT1", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Elling", desc="A weathered, bearded figure built from interlocking river stones that shift and resettle with each movement, mortared by threads of living root. Where it kneels, small stones nearby roll toward it and fuse in."}, {name="Elqoneh", desc="The stone-and-root body has grown a second, denser layer of bedrock plating, and the roots now bear small pale flowers that open and close with its breathing. Its footsteps leave patches of accelerated, unnatural growth."}, {name="Eltzabaoth", desc="A mountain given a walking shape, its bedrock body layered with visible strata recording ages it has witnessed. Forests sprout and mature in the wake of its passing, and its voice is the deep groan of tectonic plates settling."}]},
	{id="FL-MT2", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Ptahling", desc="A compact, tool-handed figure whose fingers end in small, precise implements rather than nails, always mid-adjustment of something unseen."}, {name="Ptahotep", desc="The tool-fingers have multiplied and specialized, and faint construction-lines — chalk marks for a building not yet begun — trail from its hands onto every surface it touches."}, {name="Ptahmose", desc="A craftsman-creator whose every gesture leaves behind faint architectural blueprints scored into stone, wood, and skin alike, as though it is quietly, patiently, drafting the next version of everything nearby."}]},
	{id="FL-MT3", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Vishling", desc="A four-armed, soot-marked figure constantly measuring things with tools that vanish the moment they're set down."}, {name="Vishakarna", desc="Two more arms have grown in, each holding a different half-finished instrument, and its measurements have started applying themselves — walls straighten, joints tighten, unbidden."}, {name="Vishwakarman", desc="The architect of everything given eight arms and eight tools, each one mid-strike on a different unfinished corner of reality, quietly correcting the geometry of whatever it walks past whether asked to or not."}]},
	{id="FL-MT4", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Oguling", desc="A hard-eyed, iron-scarred figure who leaves a faint rust bloom on anything metal he brushes past."}, {name="Ogunja", desc="The rust bloom has become a living patina that creeps and forms crude, useful shapes — a hook, a blade, a hinge — from whatever metal is nearby."}, {name="Ogundele", desc="An iron lord whose passage forges and unmakes metal in the same breath, leaving behind half-finished tools and weapons that seem to know, on their own, what they're for."}]},
	{id="FL-MT5", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Coaling", desc="A skirted figure whose hem seems to be woven from something that moves on its own, though it's too dim to see clearly."}, {name="Coatlique", desc="The hem is unmistakably alive now, a slow tangle of small serpentine shapes, and small stones and roots gather at her feet as if paying respects."}, {name="Coatlicueh", desc="A mother-of-all given a skirt of living serpents, giving birth to small stones and thorned growths with every slow step, the ground around her turning fertile and dangerous in the same instant."}]},
	{id="FL-MT6", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Gaialing", desc="A moss-shouldered figure whose skin shows faint cracks like dry riverbed, always slightly warm to a temperature the air doesn't explain."}, {name="Gaiamor", desc="The cracks have deepened into fissures that occasionally show a soft green glow beneath, and small growths sprout wherever she rests a hand."}, {name="Gaiaterra", desc="A world-mother whose cracked, warm body is quietly, continuously growing something new in every fissure — moss, root, ore — patient proof that matter, given enough time in her presence, prefers to become something alive."}]},
	{id="FL-MT7", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Cerning", desc="An antlered figure seated in perfect stillness, small animals treating him as part of the landscape rather than a person."}, {name="Cernunn", desc="The antlers have grown thick with moss and small nesting birds, and he no longer seems to need to move at all to be somewhere else."}, {name="Cernunnandos", desc="A horned lord who has become, functionally, a second forest — antlers a canopy, stillness a season, every creature nearby quietly certain that he was always simply part of the ground."}]},
	{id="FL-MT8", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Panguling", desc="A vast-shouldered, slow-breathing figure whose exhale has a faint mineral smell, like rain on old stone."}, {name="Pangudi", desc="Each breath now visibly stirs dust into small drifting motes that don't quite settle, and the ground beneath him has taken on faint, ancient-looking strata."}, {name="Panguhuang", desc="The world-body sleeping standing up, breath becoming wind, sweat becoming rivers, each slow heartbeat registering nearby as a barely perceptible tremor — reality's first draft, still, technically, being written."}]},
	{id="FL-PS1", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Hecatling", desc="A slight figure at a perpetual three-way crossing of paths that don't exist in the physical world, carrying a small torch of cold, colorless flame in each of three hands. It always seems to be arriving and leaving at once."}, {name="Hecatrivia", desc="A second and third silhouette have joined it, each walking a different one of the crossroads, each subtly out of sync with the others by a few seconds. The cold torches now cast light that reveals which of the observer's choices they didn't make."}, {name="Hecatepolis", desc="A trinity of identical forms standing at every crossroads simultaneously across the district, each aware of the others' thoughts. Its cold torchlight shows observers the branch of their life they abandoned, and asks — without words — whether they're certain of their choice."}]},
	{id="FL-PS2", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Hypling", desc="A heavy-lidded figure who moves with the unhurried logic of someone still partly dreaming, poppies tucked absently behind one ear."}, {name="Hypnamos", desc="The poppies have multiplied into a small drifting cloud around its head, and anyone who lingers near it starts losing track of how long they've been standing there."}, {name="Hypnostheos", desc="A god of sleep who no longer distinguishes waking from dream in his own presence, trailing an actual weather of poppy-cloud that softens edges, blurs clocks, and gently, insistently, suggests sitting down for just a moment."}]},
	{id="FL-PS3", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Mamiling", desc="A serene, water-slicked figure whose reflection in any nearby surface looks a half-second delayed and much less calm."}, {name="Mamiwara", desc="The delayed reflection has started mouthing words the figure itself hasn't said yet, always a warning, never finished in time."}, {name="Mamiwatu", desc="A river-spirit whose true self may only be the reflection — calm on the surface, frantic and honest underneath — offering wealth, secrets, or drowning with equal serenity, and never explaining which one is on offer today."}]},
	{id="FL-PS4", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Xoling", desc="A dog-headed, uneven-limbed figure that walks with a stumbling gait no injury explains, always glancing back at nothing."}, {name="Xolotlan", desc="The stumble has become a stagger between two positions at once, as if permanently one step behind its own shadow, which occasionally moves first."}, {name="Xolotecuhtli", desc="A twin-star fallen to earth in a dog's shape, dragging a second, unfinished version of itself a half-step behind at all times, and anyone who looks directly at the gap between them reports, later, dreaming only of falling."}]},
	{id="FL-PS5", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Freyling", desc="A composed, cat-attended figure whose gaze seems to already know the answer to a question not yet asked."}, {name="Freyjasol", desc="Two more cats have joined her, and her foreknowing gaze has started arriving a full sentence ahead of any conversation, finishing thoughts before they're spoken."}, {name="Freyjavana", desc="A seid-witch of unsettling foresight, cat-drawn and golden-teared, who answers questions before they're asked and asks questions whose answers the listener didn't know they already had, until she said them aloud."}]},
	{id="FL-PS6", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Ninling", desc="A soft-spoken figure who seems to be listening to a second conversation nobody else can hear."}, {name="Ninlilu", desc="The second conversation has become audible as a faint undertone beneath her actual words — always the truer of the two things she's saying at once."}, {name="Ninlilanna", desc="A grain-and-air goddess whose every sentence arrives doubled, an outer meaning and an inner one running in parallel, and the listener never quite finds out until later which one they actually agreed to."}]},
	{id="FL-PS7", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Brigling", desc="A warm, quiet figure who carries a small flame that doesn't gutter in any wind, murmuring half-finished verses under her breath."}, {name="Briginta", desc="The verses have started finishing themselves in other people's voices nearby, and the flame now casts a second, dimmer flame beside it that flickers to a different rhythm."}, {name="Brigantia", desc="A three-faced keeper of flame, verse, and healing, speaking all three at once in a single unhurried voice — whoever listens too closely finds themselves reciting the poem's ending before she reaches it herself."}]},
	{id="FL-PS8", faction="Factionless", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Bakuling", desc="A small, trunked, patchwork creature that idles near sleeping things without approaching, waiting to be invited."}, {name="Bakutan", desc="Once invited, it lingers permanently at the edge of vision, and nightmares recalled near it grow suspiciously vague, details eaten one at a time."}, {name="Bakumetsu", desc="A dream-devouring elder spirit, patchwork of borrowed nightmare-parts, whose appetite has grown selective — it no longer eats bad dreams whole, only the parts that would have taught the dreamer something."}]},
	{id="FL-QT1", faction="Factionless", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Odinling", desc="A one-eyed, cloaked silhouette trailed by two raven-shaped glitches in the air that flicker between existing and not. It seems to already know what the observer is about to do."}, {name="Odinhugin", desc="The two ravens have solidified into semi-real forms that scout ahead through short bursts of nonlinear time, returning with knowledge of events seconds before they happen. Its remaining eye has become a compound lens of a thousand futures."}, {name="Odinvalfodr", desc="An all-seeing colossus perceiving every probable outcome in its vicinity at once, its ravens now ranging minutes ahead and behind through fractured causality. It speaks answers to questions not yet asked, and its missing eye is a wound shaped like the one true future it sacrificed everything to see."}]},
	{id="FL-QT2", faction="Factionless", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Janling", desc="A two-faced figure standing exactly in doorways, one face always looking at where you came from."}, {name="Janusca", desc="Both faces now speak, one a half-second before events and one a half-second after, occasionally disagreeing about which already happened."}, {name="Janusibus", desc="A threshold-god fused to every door at once, his two faces reciting the moment just past and the moment just next in overlapping whispers — stand between them long enough and it stops being clear which one you're currently living in."}]},
